description: Bemcentinib is an inhibitor of the AXL receptor tyrosine kinase, and pembrolizumab is an anti-PD-1 antibody. In a phase II trial of bemcentinib + pembrolizumab in patients with advanced non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC), three evaluable patients with STK11 mutations demonstrated objective clinical response/clinical benefit. Additionally, preclinical data shows that AXL inhibition increases the efficacy of checkpoint blockade in STK11-deficient tumor models (Abstract: Li et al. Abstract # 602, JITC 2021. https://jitc.bmj.com/content/9/Suppl_2/A632.altmetrics).
